U.S. Gained $7.1 Billion From Mortgage Bond Wind-Down in March

-- B y   I a n   K a t z
-- 
2011-04-06T19:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/u-s-gained-7-1-billion-from-mortgage-bond-wind-down-in-march.html
U.S. taxpayers received $7.1 billion
in proceeds from the government’s wind-down of its mortgage-
backed securities last month, the Treasury Department said.  Through the end of March, taxpayers received a total of
$107.9 billion through sales and principal and interest
payments,  Mary Miller , the Treasury’s assistant secretary for
financial markets, said in a statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Katz in Washington at 
 ikatz2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Wellisz at 
 cwellisz@bloomberg.net  